description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exciting New opportunity to develop specialist skills in Acquired Brain injury Rehabilitation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a Senior Occupational Therapist to join our friendly team at Ty Aberdafen, 18 hours a week.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Situated in Llanelli, Tŷ Aberdafen is a purpose-built specialist facility, offering flexible options of specialist care and support for people with acquired brain injury and complex needs. It forms part of the UK-wide network of services provided by the Brain Injury Rehabilitation Trust (BIRT).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BIRT is the UKs leading charity providing assessment and rehabilitation services for people with acquired brain injury. We believe it is never too late to benefit from rehabilitation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you will work as part of a multidisciplinary team using the neurobehavioural model.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique community based inpatient setting with a psychological approach. The service users may have a range of complex and challenging needs including cognitive, behavioural, physical and emotional difficulties following brain injury.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have scope to work with service users in a holistic way to address all aspects of recovery and to regain maximal independence including participation in social, leisure and vocational activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is access to specialist training, supervision and development opportunities and you will be encouraged to get involved in service development and research within the trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to work flexibly, creatively and autonomously&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ideal candidate will have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-       A diploma or a degree in occupational therapy and registered with HCPC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-       At least four years post registration experience and 2 years within neurological rehabilitation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-       Experience supervising and training others&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-       A valid UK driving licence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits will include: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-       A competitive salary of £20,242&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-       38 days holiday entitlement (inclusive of bank holidays)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-       Life assurance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-       Employer pension contribution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-       Nationwide staff benefits&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please also see the Job description and Person specification for full details.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
